  description: Bisugo is a small, pinkish-white saltwater fish known for its mild
    flavor and tender white flesh. It has thin, delicate bones and is easy to clean.
    Common cooking methods include frying, steaming, or making sinigang and paksiw.
    It's a favorite for everyday Filipino home-cooked meals due to its light taste
    and affordability.
